From: Michael Tokarev <mjt@tls.msk.ru>
Subject: skip firmware blobs stripped from Debian +ds tarball
Date: Sat, 01 Apr 2023 18:46:55 +0300
Debian-Specific: yes
Forwarded: not-needed

Debian strips firmware blobs from qemu.orig.tar.gz so references
to the missing files fail during configure. This patch:
- Disables edk2 blob unpacking
- Only installs firmware blobs that actually exist on disk
- Skips dtb subdirectory (dtbs also stripped from +ds tarball)

Based on skip-unpack-edk2-blobs.patch and skip-install-dtb.patch
from the Debian qemu packaging.

diff --git a/pc-bios/meson.build b/pc-bios/meson.build
--- a/pc-bios/meson.build
+++ b/pc-bios/meson.build
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
 roms = []
-if unpack_edk2_blobs
+if unpack_edk2_blobs and false
   fds = [
     'edk2-aarch64-code.fd',
     'edk2-arm-code.fd',
@@ -86,9 +86,13 @@
 ]

 if get_option('install_blobs')
-  install_data(blobs, install_dir: qemu_datadir, install_mode: 'rw-r--r--')
+  foreach b : blobs
+    if fs.exists(b)
+      install_data(b, install_dir: qemu_datadir, install_mode: 'rw-r--r--')
+    endif
+  endforeach
 endif

 subdir('descriptors')
-subdir('dtb')
+#subdir('dtb')
 subdir('keymaps')
